item.title: HELP ME CREATE A NO-IP server!
item.dc:creator: @Giovanni9104 Giovanni9104
item.description:
@Giovanni9104 wrote:

dragster32:

okay…aps…stfu the kids right. NOW DO you have a router? beleive me you know if you have one…you’d have to go buy one at like radio shack or somewhere. The easiest way is to use ham. without a router (i hear they’re not cheap) you cant get your server online for others through no-ip. You’ll HAVE to use ham in that case. Enter hamachi.cc in your address bar and hit enter… it’ll take u to a website. Download…click create a network…make up a name…make up a pass…click okay…then have others join that network on THEIR hamachi and have them put the ip on top of your hamachi into they’re ip bar on moparisthebest.com

are you retarted? cant use no-ip without a router!!! hahahahahahah wow, you’re stupid. all you do it at no-ip, put your ip address in like you normally would! how do i know? oh yea, now i remember, cuz i ran my server without a router!!! ahahahahahahahahahaha!

ok, let me try and help.
do you have a router?
i’ll assume you do (its harder with one)
go to your routers Ip (usually 192.168.0.1 or 192.168.1.1)
look for advanced and port forwarding.
for ports, put 43594, for traffic, put TCP
then, you might need to put in your local ip (off your router) (usually 192.168.0.100 or 192.168.1.100)
do that and save your settings and check anyhting nesscisary.

STEP 2 (if you have a router, step 1 if you dont)
go to no-ip.com, log in and go to manage
click on the one you made, go to the TOP LEFT side of the page, and look for “current ip - ###.###.###.###” (the #'s are numbers like 1, 2, 3 ect)
copy that and paste it in your details on the no-ip (under ip address)
then click “modify host” at the bottom and you SHOULD be good.
